00:05:37,670 --> 00:05:40,214
because they may have to play
against each other.

109
00:05:40,965 --> 00:05:42,675
I'm dying.

110
00:05:42,759 --> 00:05:45,678
- Coach…
- What happened?

111
00:05:46,262 --> 00:05:47,847
You guys, look.

112
00:05:49,182 --> 00:05:51,726
Look at the difference, yeah?

113
00:05:52,602 --> 00:05:54,979
Poroto really wants this tournament, um,

114
00:05:55,521 --> 00:05:57,398
but the thing is Adolfo wants it too.

115
00:05:57,982 --> 00:06:01,152
You know, my husband,
even though he's doing amazing,

116
00:06:01,235 --> 00:06:03,029
he's in the retirement process.

117
00:06:03,112 --> 00:06:07,075
I'm trying to be as competitive
as I can in the next year or so.

118
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:09,327
So I think one more,
it would be great for him.

119
00:06:10,119 --> 00:06:12,080
Adolfo is very competitive.

120
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:15,500
Winning is in his DNA.

121
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:17,502
And he's the best of the best.

122
00:06:18,753 --> 00:06:19,962
Good.

123
00:06:21,130 --> 00:06:22,924
Yeah, let's go.

124
00:06:24,634 --> 00:06:28,721
People say that you're the greatest
of all time. Do you agree with that?

125
00:06:28,805 --> 00:06:32,225
I feel like there is always,
<i>always </i>somebody better than me.

126
00:06:32,308 --> 00:06:35,520
Always. But I love competing.

127
00:06:36,687 --> 00:06:39,107
Always, every day, I try to be better.

128
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:43,820
For me, to win, yes, beautiful day.

129
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:47,031
But the following day, you start
working to win the next tournament.

130
00:06:49,283 --> 00:06:50,868
My father was a surfer.

131
00:06:50,952 --> 00:06:52,703
Nothing to do with polo.

132
00:06:52,787 --> 00:06:56,040
My mother was, uh,
just a weekend polo fan.

133
00:06:57,667 --> 00:07:02,296
My first job as a professional polo player
was when I was 14.

134
00:07:03,172 --> 00:07:07,635
I was getting paid by my father
with a motorbike, so it was kind of fun.

135
00:07:10,346 --> 00:07:15,893
My friends were going out on Saturdays,
having life like a normal kid does.

136
00:07:15,977 --> 00:07:18,938
Then I was competing,
going around the world.

137
00:07:19,021 --> 00:07:20,898
I was alone, too young.

138
00:07:20,982 --> 00:07:22,442
It was tough in one moment.

139
00:07:22,984 --> 00:07:25,486
{\an8}I was very lucky

140
00:07:25,987 --> 00:07:31,075
to meet, uh, María, my wife,
when I was… 19 years old.

141
00:07:33,327 --> 00:07:35,913
I met my husband
on the cover of a magazine.

142
00:07:35,997 --> 00:07:40,460
He was, like,
they chose him as the best polo player

143
00:07:40,543 --> 00:07:41,836
and me as the best model.

144
00:07:41,919 --> 00:07:44,755
I didn't know, he was so good-looking,
so I just fell in love.

145
00:07:44,839 --> 00:07:46,883
I didn't care what he was doing, so.

146
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:54,932
So now, polo is everything
in our family and even for my children.

147
00:07:57,560 --> 00:08:00,730
In 2005,
it was a really big moment for me.

148
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:05,860
{\an8}My husband was playing
one of the final games

149
00:08:05,943 --> 00:08:08,196
of the Open in Argentina.

150
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:10,573
María was with her belly like that.

151
00:08:10,656 --> 00:08:12,450
The doctor called him.

152
00:08:13,242 --> 00:08:15,119
I was in the middle of the game.

153
00:08:15,703 --> 00:08:19,165
I was on the horse like that.
María is about to give birth.

154
00:08:19,707 --> 00:08:22,293
Adolfo's partners were asking him,

155
00:08:22,376 --> 00:08:25,421
"Please don't leave. If you leave,
maybe we're gonna lose."

156
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:30,092
I left right away with the boots
and the whites and everything.

157
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:34,347
That year, Poroto came to life.

158
00:08:36,682 --> 00:08:40,770
When Poroto was 12 years old,
I was already… 42.

159
00:08:40,853 --> 00:08:44,649
I was nearly to retire.
My back was really hurting me.

160
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:49,362
But I would see Poroto grow
as a polo player really fast.

161
00:08:49,445 --> 00:08:50,613
So I said,

162
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:53,699
"I need to play with him one day.
Why not?"

163
00:08:55,117 --> 00:08:56,994
It was the Gold Cup, we won.

164
00:08:57,745 --> 00:08:59,789
A U.S. Open. We did it, we won.

165
00:09:00,289 --> 00:09:02,542
Then we said,
"We gotta play the Argentine Open."

166
00:09:02,625 --> 00:09:04,293
<i>Adolfo.</i>

167
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:06,170
<i>Adolfo Cambiaso again.</i>

168
00:09:06,254 --> 00:09:07,588
And we did it. And we won.

169
00:09:08,172 --> 00:09:10,299
I couldn't believe
what we achieved together.

170
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:12,927
{\an8}We played together,
we won everything together.

171
00:09:13,010 --> 00:09:14,554
Now we're playing against each other.

172
00:09:22,144 --> 00:09:23,020
La Dolfina.

173
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:27,066
I think it's the best team right now.
These guys are good. They're playing well.

174
00:09:30,403 --> 00:09:34,407
I'm playing La Dolfina.
My dad is playing Valiente.

175
00:09:35,074 --> 00:09:37,660
How does it feel
to play against your son?

176
00:09:37,743 --> 00:09:39,078
Uh, it's not comfortable.

177
00:09:39,954 --> 00:09:42,123
But it's all right.

178
00:09:42,623 --> 00:09:44,542
You gotta get used to it,
but it's not easy.

179
00:09:45,501 --> 00:09:49,213
I'm really close with my dad.
We have a really good relationship.

180
00:09:49,714 --> 00:09:54,635
For me, it was a great experience
to… to share a field with my dad.

181
00:09:55,136 --> 00:09:57,722
And he's the best teacher.

182
00:09:59,348 --> 00:10:01,767
But I think that I can do more.

183
00:10:04,145 --> 00:10:07,064
Poroto is going through a stage

184
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:09,650
where he's becoming a man.

185
00:10:09,734 --> 00:10:13,154
It's time for Poroto
to start building his career

186
00:10:13,738 --> 00:10:14,780
besides Adolfo.

187
00:10:15,364 --> 00:10:18,868
It's time for him to start winning
by himself and against his father.

188
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:20,369
I think it's healthy.

189
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:22,121
I think it's about time.

190
00:10:24,874 --> 00:10:26,917
The best situation
in the U.S. Open,

191
00:10:27,001 --> 00:10:30,838
I want Valiente in the final
against our team, La Dolfina.

192
00:10:31,339 --> 00:10:33,674
The only thing that I want
is to win against him.

193
00:10:34,383 --> 00:10:36,719
I'm very proud of my son.

194
00:10:36,802 --> 00:10:38,804
But I try to beat him.

195
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:43,100
{\an8}Watch when they play each other.

196
00:10:43,184 --> 00:10:45,728
The father's not giving in.
The son's not giving in.

197
00:10:45,811 --> 00:10:47,813
They're going all out to make the plays.

198
00:10:48,648 --> 00:10:51,192
It's kind of drama,
to be honest, for all of us.

199
00:10:51,984 --> 00:10:56,656
But the good thing is
if they get there to that final game,

200
00:10:56,739 --> 00:10:58,282
a Cambiaso will win.

201
00:11:05,373 --> 00:11:07,375
{\an8}

202
00:11:08,876 --> 00:11:12,171
Does everyone want
to beat the Cambiasos as bad as you do?

203
00:11:12,254 --> 00:11:14,924
As bad as I do? I don't think so.

204
00:11:17,677 --> 00:11:20,429
The Cambiasos have a target
on their back because they always win.

205
00:11:21,013 --> 00:11:24,934
